197,203,209,214,255,269,275,280,291,297,302,308,313,324,330,335,341,346,354,376,381,387,392,401,412,417],{"type":182,"tag":183,"props":184,"children":186},"element","h2",{"id":185},"quick-questions",[187],{"type":188,"value":189},"text","Quick Questions",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":192,"children":194},"h4",{"id":193},"gitflow-是什么",[195],{"type":188,"value":196},"Gitflow 是什么？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":199,"children":200},"p",{},[201],{"type":188,"value":202},"Gitflow 是一种使用 Git 合作时使用的工作流程。与之类似的概念有 Centralized Workflow、Feature Branch Workflow、Forking Workflow 等。",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":204,"children":206},{"id":205},"选用工作流前需要注意什么",[207],{"type":188,"value":208},"选用工作流前需要注意什么？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":210,"children":211},{},[212],{"type":188,"value":213},"工作流应该是“指南”，而不是手册，没有一种工作流程是能解决所有问题而没有显著副作用的，所以应该根据团队规模、业务流程（如需求大小、需求频次）选用更适合团队的工作流。",{"type":182,"tag":215,"props":216,"children":217},"ul",{},[218,232,244],{"type":182,"tag":219,"props":220,"children":221},"li",{},[222,224,230],{"type":188,"value":223},"工作流能否",{"type":182,"tag":225,"props":226,"children":227},"strong",{},[228],{"type":188,"value":229},"容错",{"type":188,"value":231},"，或是可以避免犯错？",{"type":182,"tag":219,"props":233,"children":234},{},[235,237,242],{"type":188,"value":236},"工作流能否可以随着团队人数变更而",{"type":182,"tag":225,"props":238,"children":239},{},[240],{"type":188,"value":241},"扩展",{"type":188,"value":243},"？",{"type":182,"tag":219,"props":245,"children":246},{},[247,249,254],{"type":188,"value":248},"工作流能否带来了不必要的",{"type":182,"tag":225,"props":250,"children":251},{},[252],{"type":188,"value":253},"认知负担",{"type":188,"value":243},{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":256,"children":257},{},[258,260],{"type":188,"value":259},"见：",{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":262,"children":266},"a",{"href":263,"rel":264},"http://fresky.github.io/2020/03/10/common-branching-models/",[265],"nofollow",[267],{"type":188,"value":268},"常见的代码分支模型和比较",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":270,"children":272},{"id":271},"centralized-workflow-是怎么运作的",[273],{"type":188,"value":274},"Centralized Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":276,"children":277},{},[278],{"type":188,"value":279},"如果其他版本管理工具过渡到 Git，那么 Centralized Workflow 是学习成本最小的方案。在此工作流中，团队成员围绕 main 分支开发：拉取代码、开发，然后提交，就这么简单。因为没有额外的分支，所以 main 分支的历史记录开起来像是一条干净的线，这种感觉就像是传统的 SVN 工作流一样。",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":281,"children":282},{},[283,284],{"type":188,"value":259},{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":285,"children":288},{"href":286,"rel":287},"https://trunkbaseddevelopment.com/",[265],[289],{"type":188,"value":290},"Trunk Based Development",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":292,"children":294},{"id":293},"feature-branch-workflow-是怎么运作的",[295],{"type":188,"value":296},"Feature Branch Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":298,"children":299},{},[300],{"type":188,"value":301},"Feature Branch Workflow 是在 Centraolized Workflow 之上的扩展。开发人员在单独的 feature 分支开发新功能，然后通过 PR 请求提交回 main 分支。在需要帮助时，可以提前请求 PR，邀请他们代码审阅或是提交修复。这种流程隐含的约定是：main 分支上的代码一定是可用的（至少测试通过，能跑），这种小步快跑的模式对持续集成环境来说是一个巨大的优势。",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":303,"children":305},{"id":304},"pr-是什么",[306],{"type":188,"value":307},"PR 是什么？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":309,"children":310},{},[311],{"type":188,"value":312},"Pull Request（PR）是一种使用 GitLab 或其它版本管理系统附带的一种工作流程。PR 可以作为一种告知团队其它成员当前分支功能已经完成的提醒。每个 PR 还附带有代码变更内容和讨论区，团队成员可以通过 PR 进行 Code Review，讨论方案，或者评论代码。使开发人员从邮件或者即时通讯软件中解脱出来。",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":314,"children":315},{},[316,317],{"type":188,"value":259},{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":318,"children":321},{"href":319,"rel":320},"https://guides.github.com/introduction/flow/",[265],[322],{"type":188,"value":323},"GitHub flow",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":325,"children":327},{"id":326},"forking-workflow-是怎么运作的",[328],{"type":188,"value":329},"Forking Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":331,"children":332},{},[333],{"type":188,"value":334},"在 Forking Workflow 流程中，开发使用单独的仓库来开发一个完整的功能，一旦功能开发完毕，再通过 PR 合并回主仓库 main 分支。因为主仓库管理员并不关心代码的具体实现，所以开发没有主仓库的写入权限，Code Review 也不用在主仓库进行。",{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":336,"children":338},{"id":337},"gitflow-workflow-是怎么运作的",[339],{"type":188,"value":340},"Gitflow Workflow 是怎么运作的？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":342,"children":343},{},[344],{"type":188,"value":345},"Gitflow Workflow 最早在 Vincent Driessen 2010 年写的一篇博客中被提出。作为 Feature Branch Workflow 的补充，它仅仅是规范各分支的行为。不同分支有不同的作用，比方说 release 分支用来测试，main 分支用来发布，hotfix 分支用来提交热修复，等等。Gitflow 还规定了分支与分支应该如何合并。",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":347,"children":348},{},[349],{"type":182,"tag":350,"props":351,"children":353},"img",{"alt":176,"src":352},"https://mgear-image.oss-cn-shanghai.aliyuncs.com/image/other/20220627173845.png?w=40",[],{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":355,"children":356},{},[357,358,365,367,374],{"type":188,"value":259},{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":359,"children":362},{"href":360,"rel":361},"https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/comparing-workflows/gitflow-workflow",[265],[363],{"type":188,"value":364},"Gitflow Workflow",{"type":188,"value":366},"、",{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":368,"children":371},{"href":369,"rel":370},"https://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/",[265],[372],{"type":188,"value":373},"A successful Git branching model",{"type":188,"value":375},"，在 2020 年的补充中，作者提及类似 Web 应用这种不需要经常回滚的应用，使用更简单的 GitHub Flow 可能会更合适。",{"type":182,"tag":183,"props":377,"children":379},{"id":378},"评价",[380],{"type":188,"value":378},{"type":182,"tag":191,"props":382,"children":384},{"id":383},"gitflow-的负面影响",[385],{"type":188,"value":386},"Gitflow 的负面影响？",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":388,"children":389},{},[390],{"type":188,"value":391},"Thoughtworks 认为短生命周期的分支策略给实施 CI/CD 带来更小的伤害，反之类似 Gitflow 中经常用到的长生命周期分治策略反而是在鼓励后期集成（late integration）。",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":393,"children":394},{},[395],{"type":182,"tag":396,"props":397,"children":398},"q",{},[399],{"type":188,"value":400},"We firmly believe that long-lived version-control branches harm valuable engineering practieces such as CI, and this belief underlies our dislike for Gitflow.",{"type":182,"tag":198,"props":402,"children":403},{},[404,405],{"type":188,"value":259},{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":406,"children":409},{"href":407,"rel":408},"https://www.thoughtworks.com/cn/radar/techniques/long-lived-branches-with-gitflow",[265],[410],{"type":188,"value":411},"Gitflow long-lived-branch on Tech Radar",{"type":182,"tag":183,"props":413,"children":415},{"id":414},"相关资源",[416],{"type":188,"value":414},{"type":182,"tag":215,"props":418,"children":419},{},[420,430],{"type":182,"tag":219,"props":421,"children":422},{},[423],{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":424,"children":427},{"href":425,"rel":426},"https://devblogs.microsoft.com/oldnewthing/20180323-01/?p=98325",[265],[428],{"type":188,"value":429},"Stop cherry-picking, start merging",{"type":182,"tag":219,"props":431,"children":432},{},[433],{"type":182,"tag":261,"props":434,"children":437},{"href":435,"rel":436},"https://martinfowler.com/articles/branching-patterns.html",[265],[438],{"type":188,"value":439},"Patterns for Managing Source Code Branches",{"title":175,"searchDepth":441,"depth":441,"links":442},2,[443,444,445],{"id":185,"depth":441,"text":189},{"id":378,"depth":441,"text":378},{"id":414,"depth":441,"text":414},"markdown","content:6.maps:_devops:git:gitflow.md","content","6.maps/_devops/git/gitflow.md","6.maps/_devops/git/gitflow","md",[453,457],{"_path":454,"title":455,"description":456},"/maps/_devops/git/dorothy","Dorothy","Dorothy 是我的 Git Commit Message 的约定。",{"_path":458,"title":459,"description":460},"/maps/_devops/git/pre-commit-hook","Pre Commit Hook","title: 预提交钩子（Pre-commit hooks）\ndescription: Git 的 pre-commit hook 用来在提交代码前执行一些检查或操作",1771214954939]